title.Name: title
title.Value: Rosco the Berner - Dog Show 3 (Owning the Ring)

description.Name: description
description.Value:
Yeah... it is not what you think. Funny thing is he came out of this still winning points. This is the final of three clips showing our Berner "Rosco" in action at a dog show. Somehow Rosco manages to give 'action' a different meaning.

Rosco is a Bernese Mountain Dog (as in Bern, Switzerland) who we got from Nobleheart Kennels. He was just over a year old in this clip. In Canada, a dog needs a minimum of 10 points awarded from at least three judges to get 'Champion' status; Rosco earned 12 points in two dog shows. Keep in mind each dog show is run over three days with a different judge for each day and points are awarded based on conforming with the breed standard and on the number of other dogs beaten out for the win.
